TITLE: Lordstown Motors says it still has $220 million in cash as it grapples with production issues and an EV pivot
SUMMARY: Lordstown ended the year with over $220 million in cash as it pivots to work with Foxconn on a new electric vehicle program.

TITLE: SiriusXM cuts 8% of its workforce as part of a broader reorganization
SUMMARY: SiriusXM CEO Jennifer Witz told staff on Monday the company is cutting 8% of its workforce, or 475 roles.

TITLE: Marlboro maker Altria agrees to buy e-cigarette startup NJOY for nearly $2.8 billion
SUMMARY: Altria's deal to buy NJOY comes after the Marlboro maker exited its position in Juul Labs.

TITLE: Nestle, Tyson and other food giants bet on air fryer boom to grow sales
SUMMARY: U.S. consumers spent nearly $1 billion last year buying air fryers, up 51% from 2019.

TITLE: ESPN wants to be the hub of all live sports streaming — even if it helps its competition
SUMMARY: The idea aims to make ESPN the TV guide of live sports. The network has held talks with major leagues and media companies, sources said.

TITLE: How top women executives in sports and betting are leading by example
SUMMARY: At the MIT Sloan Sports Analytics conference, sports betting and diversity are among the themes this year.

TITLE: Mortgage rates jump back over 7% as inflation fears drive yields higher
SUMMARY: Growing fears that inflation is not cooling off are pushing bond yields higher. Mortgage rates loosely follow the yield on the U.S. 10-year Treasury.

TITLE: Nordstrom earnings top expectations as retailer starts winding down Canada operations
SUMMARY: Nordstrom has struggled with slower sales, more markdowns and pressure from activist investor Ryan Cohen.

TITLE: Ford plans to restart production of the electric F-150 Lightning on March 13
SUMMARY: Ford plans to restart production of its electric F-150 Lightning pickup on March 13 – more than a month after a battery issue caused a vehicle to catch fire.

TITLE: Leylah Fernandez urges athletes to become financially literate as soon as possible
SUMMARY: Leylah Fernandez spoke to CNBC about the importance of preparing for life after tennis.

TITLE: Millions of low-income families could soon face steeper broadband internet bills
SUMMARY: Low-income households that have relied on a federal broadband subsidy for the past two years could see their internet bills rise if the program is not renewed.

TITLE: Macy's shares jump after holiday-quarter profit tops expectations
SUMMARY: Macy's delivered a bigger profit than expected during the holiday quarter.

TITLE: Ford sales jump as supply chain issues improve
SUMMARY: Sales of Ford's F-Series pickups increased 22% last month compared with a year earlier, including a spike in sales of its electric F-150 Lightning.

TITLE: Polestar cuts annual losses in half as it ramps up EV production
SUMMARY: Polestar's relatively positive results come after other EV startups like Lucid, Nikola and Rivian reported ongoing problems with supply chains and production.

TITLE: Best Buy tops holiday-quarter expectations but warns of further sales declines in the coming year
SUMMARY: Best Buy posted earnings and revenue that beat analysts' estimates for its holiday quarter.

TITLE: SpaceX launches Crew-6 mission for NASA, sending four more astronauts to the space station
SUMMARY: SpaceX launched four people from Florida as Elon Musk's company begins the final of the original six missions awarded by NASA.

TITLE: Sen. Bernie Sanders calls vote on possible subpoena for Starbucks CEO Howard Schultz over allegations of union-busting
SUMMARY: Starbucks CEO Howard Schultz previously declined to appear at the Senate hearing on allegations of union-busting.

TITLE: Delta pilots approve new contract with 34% raises
SUMMARY: The deal for Delta pilots includes 34% raises over the next four years.

TITLE: Those Il Makiage makeup ads are everywhere — here's the story behind them
SUMMARY: Oddity, which created DTC beauty and wellness brands Il Makiage and Spoiled Child, says it's profitable. Experts think it could be preparing for an IPO.

TITLE: Lowe's offers soft sales outlook, warning of a 'cautious consumer'
SUMMARY: Lowe's issued a conservative outlook for the next fiscal year as the home improvement sector faces pressure from a shift in consumer spending.

TITLE: Mortgage demand from homebuyers drops to a 28-year low
SUMMARY: Mortgage demand dropped for the third straight week as interest rates moved higher again.

TITLE: Schumer, Jeffries pressure Murdoch, Fox News over Trump's false election fraud claims
SUMMARY: Chuck Schumer and Hakeem Jeffries are calling foul on Rupert Murdoch following Dominion Voting Systems' latest Fox News revelations.

TITLE: Kohl's posts surprising holiday-quarter loss, offers weak sales outlook
SUMMARY: Kohl's sales for the holiday quarter came in well below Wall Street's expectations.

TITLE: Peloton hires former Twitter executive Dalana Brand to be chief people officer
SUMMARY: Dalana Brand, the former chief people and diversity officer at Twitter, has been tapped as Peloton's new chief people officer.

TITLE: MSG Networks to launch streaming service for Knicks, Rangers games
SUMMARY: MSG is the latest regional sports network to launch a streaming service

TITLE: Netflix announces a 'Stranger Things' stage play is coming to London's West End
SUMMARY: The play joins a growing array of in-person events inspired by Netflix films and shows like "Bridgerton" and "Glass Onion: A Knives Out Mystery."

TITLE: Aston Martin shares surge 14% on profitability forecast for 2023
SUMMARY: Shares of British luxury carmaker Aston Martin Lagonda surged, as the company's positive 2023 guidance offset pretax losses last year.

TITLE: General Motors cuts 500 salaried employees
SUMMARY: GM follows other major companies, including competitors, in downsizing headcounts to preserve cash and boost profits.

TITLE: Target leans into 'affordable joy' and its cheap chic reputation as sales slow
SUMMARY: Target is investing money in new services and brands that it hopes will convince more budget-conscious customers to boost spending at the retailer.

TITLE: Rivian posts mixed fourth quarter and underwhelming EV production outlook, stock falls
SUMMARY: The results follow slower-than-expected production, unexpected pricing pressure and plans to lay off 6% of its workforce in a bid to conserve cash.
